				 Isolated rain alert 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								The Met office on Sunday warned of isolated rain or a thundershower in Calcutta and the rest of south Bengal in the next 24 hours.																								G.C. Debnath, the director of the weather section at the Regional Meteorological Centre, in Alipore, said the cyclonic circulation (anti-clockwise movement of air) that had formed over the east-central Bay of Bengal on Saturday, weakened on Sunday.																								But despite the weakening of the cyclonic formation, a lot of clouds could be seen over the east-central Bay of Bengal. We are watching the development, said an official.																								The monsoon, he added, is yet to withdraw from Bengal.
